'''Teoman Koman''' ({{circa|1936}} <U+2013> 14 December 2013) was a [[Turkey|Turkish]] general who retired in 1997.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldbulletin.net/?aType=haber&ArticleID=124954 |title=Turkish coup general Teoman Koman dies |publisher=World Bulletin |date= |accessdate=2013-12-16}}</ref> He was [[List of General Commanders of the Gendarmerie of Turkey|General Commander of the Gendarmerie of Turkey]] (1995 - 1997) and previously head of the [[National Intelligence Organization (Turkey)|National Intelligence Organization]] (1988 - 1992) and Deputy Secretary-General of the [[National Security Council (Turkey)|National Security Council]] (1986 - 1988). 

Koman was charged with being involved with the [[1997 military memorandum (Turkey)|1997 "post-modern coup"]].<ref name=TZ>[[Today's Zaman]], 22 October 2012, [http://www.todayszaman.com/newsDetail_getNewsById.action?newsId=296056 Retired Gen. Koman says he banned J<U+0130>TEM activities]</ref> Koman told the [[Ergenekon trials]] that he was aware of the existence of the [[JITEM]] Gendarmerie unit during his tenure, and that it was an unofficial association of Gendarmerie members, which he had banned.<ref name=TZ/>

